human

Class Patient

  • java.lang.Object
    • human.Patient

  • public class Patient
extends Object
    The patient is defined by different variables:
    name
    surname
    ID
    health insurance
    security level
    state (generated by default)
    location (null by default)
    history (empty arraylist by default)
    arrival time
    assigned physician (null by default)
    bill
    destination
    ED

               String name,

               int arrivalTime)
        This constructs a patient with given name and surname and trigger the PatientArrival event before adding it to the GeneratedPatients list
        Parameters:
        EDname - The ED in which you wish to construct this patient
        name - the name of this patient
        surname - the surname of this patient
        healthInsurance - the kind of health insurrance the patient has
        severityLevel - The security level of this patient
        arrivalTime - The time at which this patient arrived to the ED
